            "ratingValue": "4",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I studied in this school long ago (1996-2002). I have wonderful memories. The only thing I didn't like was that all students are not treated in the same way when it comes to dealing with interests other than core subjects, be it music, arts or sports. No equal opportunity in neither competitions nor training is given for the said subjects. I also heard that school standards related to discipline and hygiene had deteriorated after the right to education was implemented. Usage of foul language is also much now. There was a formation of groups based on the region a student belongs. Teachers are also interested in tutoring services than improving the school standards. but this school is better than many KVs in vizag.",
